grid.text: 8. Waki is kneeling between the Otsuzumi and Kotsuzumi players, facing the back.
4. Pick up the wand in his R hand
4. Hold the wand at R. arm length before bringing it down to his side.
sono shoku no homare wo kō-muru

captions.translation: [WAKI] Now, I, Munichika, in compliance with the Imperial Will
have accordingly ascended the dais to ward off impurities.
It is adorned with the Seven-fold Sacred Rope,
captions.transcription: fujō wo hedatsuru nanae no shime
captions.japaneseScript: 不浄を隔つる七重の注連

captions.translation: and in the four corners sacred images placed in reverence.
captions.transcription: shi-hō ni honzon no kake tatematsuri
captions.japaneseScript: 四方に本尊をかけ奉り

captions.translation: I raise up this Sacred wand and make my petition.
captions.japaneseScript: 幣帛を捧げ　仰ぎ願はくは

captions.translation: Now, in the reign of the Sixty-sixth Emperor Ichijo,
I have been honored greatly in my craft,
through no effort of my own,
captions.transcription: sono shoku no homare wo kō-muru koto

captions.translation: rather, I have held in trust those skills.
captions.transcription: kore watakushi no chikara ni arazu.

captions.translation: When Izanagi and Izanami crossed over

captions.japaneseScript: 天の浮橋を踏みわたり

captions.translation: and probed the Abundant Reed Plain
with the Sacred Spear was their beginning.
Later, from holy Hashimida of Eastern India
captions.transcription: Sono nochi Nansen sōkada koku basshi
captions.japaneseScript: その後南瞻僧伽陀国波斯

captions.translation: the descendants of Amakuni and Fujito

captions.transcription: Amakuni Fujito no shison ni tsutaete
captions.japaneseScript: 天国ひつきの子孫に伝へて

captions.translation: which I am now the master of.
